  "prompt": "What is the coefficient of Friction value for turcite on steel and turcite on turcite?",
  "response": "Turcite is a type of low-friction bearing material, often used in applications where reduced friction and wear are important. The coefficient of friction can vary based on the specific grades of Turcite and the surface finishes involved, but general values can be provided:\n\n1. **Turcite on Steel:** The coefficient of friction for Turcite against steel typically ranges from **0.1 to 0.2** (static) and can be slightly lower for dynamic friction.\n\n2. **Turcite on Turcite:** The coefficient of friction for Turcite sliding against another Turcite surface generally ranges from **0.1 to 0.15**.\n\nThese values are approximate and actual performance can be influenced by factors such as load, speed, lubrication, surface roughness, and environmental conditions. It is always advisable to consult specific material datasheets or perform testing under expected conditions for precise applications.",
